{"author":{"id":"144ad87499f23e542ca19f06c7fd2eff0a1056f0f72b792d2cb236eca4d75d06"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1505772053,"nonce":"P2VVCp2wa9eeT5RsyC4yyy2fLDg=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMzMDM2ODgzMg==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1478#issuecomment-330368832"},"message":"Hi @NCEichner,\n\nI took a look to see if the changes I've added in the PR to fix the strandedness bug will fix this issue, but unfortunately they won't :(\n\nI think I can see what the problem is - it looks like nested inputs don't work with Rename Datasets?\n\nIn the Workflow Editor Rename Dataset section, for paired reads you get these \"Valid Inputs\" listed:\n\n_for Bowtie2:_ \nlibrary|input_1,  library|input_2\n(renaming works using #{input_1|basename}.bam)\n\n_for HISAT2:_ \ninput_format|paired|collection|forward, input_format|paired|collection|reverse.\n(renaming does not work using #{forward|basename}.bam)\n\n_for HISAT2 new PR:_\nreads|library|input_1, reads|library|input_2\n(renaming does not work using #{input_1|basename}.bam, but does work if I remove the section called \"reads\", a section I added for cosmetic purposes)\n\nSo I think to fix this issue the options are:\n\n- the HISAT2 wrapper needs to be changed to not use a nested input variable (that would make it work similarly to Bowtie2. But does Bowtie2 handle renaming of paired collections? it looks like it might not from here: https://biostar.usegalaxy.org/p/14911/)\n- the Galaxy codebase needs to be changed (or maybe hack the code yourself like some people did here https://github.com/galaxyproject/galaxy/issues/1675)\n- find another way to do the sample renaming \n\nIf anyone in IUC has a suggestion would be great to hear as it would be really good to get this renaming outputs working.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1506484836,"nonce":"ae3Fj9dmyLG3erkWlmO52CCTFIU=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMzMjQwMjMzOA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1478#issuecomment-332402338"},"message":"@NCEichner, this issue should also be fixed now in the newest HISAT2 from the toolshed here: https://toolshed.g2.bx.psu.edu/repository?repository_id=c864c7c00326f71d\u0026changeset_revision=d5fe9aead222","files":null}]}